# 🐧 Linux & Bash Scripting

This directory contains my Bash scripting exercises and mini-projects completed while learning Linux scripting from scratch.

The goal of these exercises is to understand Bash syntax, Linux command-line automation, and basic scripting logic by writing scripts without relying on copy-paste solutions.

---

# 📚 Topics Covered

## Variables & User Input

- Variables
- User input using `read`
- Output using `echo`
- Command substitution (`$(...)`)

## Conditional Statements

- `if`
- `elif`
- `else`
- Numeric comparisons (`-eq`, `-gt`, `-lt`, `-ge`, `-le`, `-ne`)
- String comparisons
- File tests:
  - `-e` (exists)
  - `-d` (directory)
  - `-r` (readable)
  - `-w` (writable)
  - `-x` (executable)
  - `-s` (not empty)

## Case Statements

- Interactive menus
- User input handling
- Multiple-choice execution

## For Loops

- Iterating through lists
- Iterating through numeric ranges
- Arithmetic `for` loops
- Iterating through command output
- Nested loops (basic understanding)

